The paper involves using data-driven techniques to plan for low budget yet high return new movies by learning from previous movies. This involves utilizing an online movie knowledge library and historical collaboration records to estimate acquaintance scores of movie configuration factors. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Databases (cs.DB), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
